Woodward has come under fire as several big-money signings and a trio of managers have underperformed since Ferguson's retirement in 2013, the last time United won the league title.<\/p>\r\n\r\n

The club, which has suffered a more-than-seven-percent drop in its share price this year, also stands to lose ground to European rivals off the field.<\/p>\r\n\r\n

Spanish giant FC Barcelona last week reported 990 million euros ($1.1bn) in turnover for 2018-19 and expects to surpass one billion euros this year, while domestic rivals Manchester City and Liverpool are also breathing down United's neck.<\/p>\r\n\r\n

